<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900719-0034</DOCNO><DOCID>900719-0034.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Daimler-Benz AG:   Workers at Mercedes Unit   Agree to Overtime Shifts</HL><DATE>07/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   G.DAI LABOR</CO><LP>   Mercedes-Benz AG said the company's workers' councilagreed to special Saturday overtime shifts to help thecompany cope with rising demand.   The auto-making arm of Daimler-Benz AG said that specialshifts will be added on &quot;several Saturdays&quot; beginningSeptember. The overtime shifts will affect the company'splants in Stuttgart-Untertuerkheim, Sindelfingen and Bremen.</LP><TEXT>   Mercedes-Benz had tried to introduce the overtime shiftsat the start of the year, but the company couldn't reach anagreement with the workers' council   In a statement, Mercedes-Benz said the extra shifts willbe added &quot;so that the company can react flexibly to theheightened demand.&quot; It said that &quot;clear&quot; growth rates inEurope and in other foreign markets for Mercedes-Benz cars ingeneral, along with lively demand for certain models and forequipment, had prompted the need for extra shifts.</TEXT></DOC>